• Hỗ trợ Cán bộ, công nhân viên trong công tác sử dụng, vận hành hệ thống CNTT, xử lý các sự vụ CNTT liên quan hệ thống mạng, thoại, camera, phát thanh… và hệ thống phần mềm đảm bảo hỗ trợ người dùng trong khai thác CNTT;
• Kiểm soát, thiết lập an toàn thông tin, tổ chức sao lưu dữ liệu định kỳ, phòng chống tấn công mạng, thực hiện các nghiệp vụ bảo mật, cấp phát phân quyền;
• Nghiên cứu, triển khai khai các giải pháp CNTT mới trong công tác quản lý bảo mật và công nghệ
• Phối hợp với các đối tác, nhà cung cấp dịch vụ CNTT, viễn thông trong công tác quản lý, triển khai, áp dụng CNTT;
• Hướng dẫn, dào tạo Cán bộ, công nhân viên các quy định và hướng dẫn sử dụng, áp dung, vận hành hệ thống CNTT.

**Position Summary and Key Goals**
Provide daily support and counseling for all business units (Animal Nutrition, Agriculture Services, Human Nutrition, and Carbohydrate Solution) and supporting functions (Procurement, Regulations, Operation (Production), Supply Chain, HR, etc.) in Vietnam. Supervise and ensure compliance with local regulations and the company’s policies by all business units and supporting functions. Directly report to Senior Legal Counsel, Animal Nutrition APAC, Vietnam cum Vietnam Legal Counsel (all VN business units).
**Key Goals:**
Providing proactive and effective commercially focused legal support for ADM’s business operation in Vietnam.
**YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES**
• Respond to and assist with daily questions and requests of business units and functions in Vietnam;
• Draft, review, advise on, and negotiate contracts and other legal documents to support daily operation of the business;
• Review and update standard contract templates and better contract review and filing processes.
• Supervise and be in charge of corporate works of the local entities, including but not limited to updating corporate documents, obtaining business licenses, permits, certificates from time to time, and archiving the same;
• Partnering with other corporate functions to protect company’s interests and contribute to and deliver company’s goals and developments;
• Assist Senior Counsels in providing legal advice and counselling to the local businesses;
• Assist Senior Counsel in mergers and acquisitions, strategic alliances, joint ventures, and other corporate transactions and corporate restructuring in Vietnam;
• Cooperate with US/EMEA headquarters Legal & Compliance functions where necessary;
• Perform all other legal and compliance-related responsibility as necessary and as directed by senior counsel.

Job Requirements:
Education:
• Bachelor of Laws (LLB) at reputable law school and prefer a Master of Laws (LLM) or a qualified lawyer in Vietnam;
Experience:
• Around 5 years of experience in international law firms or leading domestic law firms (specialized in Corporate, M&A, labor; experience in dispute resolution is a plus); in-house experience with MNCs in similar industry would be preferred but not necessary.
Skills:
• Have a business-oriented, practical, solution-oriented mindset and analytical and negotiation skills;
• Good communication skills to interact, develop, and maintain a good relationship with internal and external clients and drive desirable outcomes through influence;
• High degree of self-management to work proactively and independently, contribute to teamwork, and be able to determine and prioritize matters efficiently;
• High understanding and sense of compliance (including anti-corruption, anti-bribery, trade sanctions, and anti-trust);
• Flexibility with traveling domestically upon demand;
• Highest ethical standards and strong integrity;
• Native in Vietnamese and fluent in both verbal and written English.
Other required or desirable attributes:
• Outgoing, self-motivated, self-disciplined, and team-oriented;
• Committed to ADM values: integrity, respect, excellence, resourcefulness, teamwork, and responsibility;
• High awareness and of compliance with general supervision and direction from direct manager and dotted-line manager in furtherance of legal and compliance standards and goals;
• Ability to work under pressure in a fast-paced and dynamic environment while handling multiple competing tasks simultaneously to closure.

Job Description:
Duties and Responsibilities:
1. Building relationships with key stakeholders of each prospect (e.g: university, information center, etc) to promote relevant products, then closing the deal by contract;
2. Gaining product knowledge through product training, assisting sales managers with paperwork or customer support tasks, events, and workshops;
3. Gradually develop sales strategies and coordinate cross-functional support to help customers maximize the value of products, services, or solutions provided by iGroup;
4. Regular reports for monthly marketing and sales activities on our CRM system (Monday.com);
5. Maintain up-to-date knowledge of industry trends and competitors;
6. Explore and attend workshops and events in the education or research field to get more prospects.

- Chịu trách nhiệm tính toán hiệu quả đầu tư của dự án, lập kế hoạch ngân sách, phân bổ dòng tiền cho dự án hoạt động, kinh doanh và phát triển các dự án bất động sản;
- Lập Báo cáo nghiên cứu tiền khả thi, hồ sơ đề xuất xin chấp thuận chủ trương đầu tư dự án; Hồ sơ đấu giá quyền sử dụng đất; Hồ sơ đấu thầu lựa chọn Nhà đầu tư dự án đầu tư có sử dụng đất.
- Thực hiện các công tác liên quan tới lập phương án, tính chi phí trong công tác hỗ trợ, đền bù GPMB, làm việc với cơ quan quản lý nhà nước cũng như địa phương trong các công việc liên quan tới tính toán chi phí GPMB của dự án;
